    "updated_at": "2014-10-13T18:12:11Z",
    "body": "Faced this issue also, my fix is to add an forward slash for just after the protocol when loading the url of the browser window\n`asar:/c:/Atom/app.asar/index.html`\nadditionally, for my usage, i change the backslash from the `__dirname` to forward slash\n`__dirname.replace(/\\\\/gi,'/')`\n\nThus in code, my browser window load code is something like, works for OSX and Windows:\n\n```\nvar dirResource = __dirname.replace(/\\\\/gi,'/');\n// Check to make sure dirname starts with a forward slash else append a forward slash\nif ( dirResource.indexOf('/') !== 0 ) {\n   dirResource = '/' + dirResource;\n}\nmainWindow.loadUrl('asar:' + dirResource + '/app.asar/index.html');\n```\n"
